meanings.definition: To pull or drag out more than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The determined little ant outpulled the big beetle to reach the food first.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outpulled his competitor in the tug-of-war game.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outpulled the bird in the seed gathering contest.
meanings.sent4: The tiny tugboat outpulled the massive ship in the race to the harbor.
meanings.sent5: The determined child outpulled the stubborn dog to move the heavy box.
